{
  "texts": [
    "• Are there any differences between the chatbots in terms of developing lesson plans?",
    "• What are the characteristics of the responses based on learning theories and models?",
    "LITERATURE REVIEW and THEORETICAL FRAMEWORK Lesson plans are simply drafts of a course.",
    "Lesson plans are important for teachers' class activities (Ball & Cohen, 1996) and they are essential guidelines for student teachers (Rusznyak & Walton, 2011).",
    "These drafts should have learning objectives (what participants are expected to learn), learning activities (how teaching and learning take place), and materials (resources to use during instruction)."
  ]
}